• Can Now Host 500 Guests Or 50 Per Cent Capacity
• Ceremonies Allowed To Hold For Six Hours Lagos State Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu has announced the easing of restrictions on social and event centres, who are allowed to operate for only six hours and 50 per cent capacity or 500 guests ceiling.  They disclosed that the event duration should not exceed six hours, with all guests and service providers at the facility wearing nose mask, must make use of hand sanitizers, and temperature checks taken at all entry points into a facility.  
 
“Guests and service providers with a temperature above 37.5 are to be politely turned back and referred to paramedics or the emergency response team on the ground.  “Safety Marshals shall be deployed by an accredited event safety consultant from the Commission for every social event with attendance exceeding 200 people.” To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .